Thane Municipal Election Results 2017 Live Updates: Counting begins Thane Municipal Election Results 2017 Live Updates: Counting begins Thane Municipal Corporation election results: The contest chiefly is between the BJP, Shiv Sena and the NCP. By: Express Web Desk | New Delhi | Updated: February 23, 2017 10:15 am A policeman guards Electronic Voting Machines (EVM) at a training camp in Thane on Monday (PTI Photo) 
The counting of results of the elections to the Thane Municipal Corporation began at 10 am. The battle chiefly is between the BJP, Shiv Sena and the NCP. Voter turnout in Thane was 58 per cent during polling. There are 130 seats at stake here. Â© The Indian Express Online Media Pvt Ltd Tags:
